Murray Hill Building Company, Inc., a New York corporation, v. The F. H. Smith Company, a Delaware corporation. (September 22, 1931.)

Pennewill, C. J., Harrington and Richards, J. J., sitting.

James R. Morford (of Marvel, Morford, Ward. and Logan) for plaintiff. Caleb S. Layton (of Richards, Layton and Finger) for defendant. Superior Court for New Castle County, No. 26,

September Term, 1931.

*17The court

held the plea good and overruled the demurrer thereto.
